description: We arrived in St. Petersburg and for the first time in a long time this city did not seem friendly to me. The streets are full of snow and ice, darkness and mud are everywhere. This is my home and many of my friends are here, but I felt that I did not want to come here in winter or live here. I still admire the beauty of this city, its chaos, but I felt abandoned, and I hope that next time in the spring or summer it will pass. There was a broken tiger chair in the yard near the dump. It smiled at me, and I went back to it to take this picture.
